  "body": "#### System information\r\n\r\nGeth version: 1.7.2 and 1.7.3, others untested\r\nOS & Version: Windows 10 build 16299.98\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\n`geth --light` or `geth --syncmode light` would behave as expected\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\nI run geth like this: `\".\\geth\\geth.exe\" --light --datadir \".\\geth\\data\" --verbosity 5`. The client is never able to connect to any peers. Without the verbosity flag, the client stops printing entirely, but with it the client shows a lot of errors. \r\n\r\nI have both geth fully allowed in Windows firewall on all networks and protocols. I also tried `--v5disc` since the issues seem to be with peer discovery but that didn't do anything. My issue seems similar to #15266. \r\n\r\nHere is the log with verbosity 4: https://gist.github.com/ajthemacboy/23e5e4b0a07fcc00089301d001795996\r\nAnd here is another one with verbosity 5: https://gist.github.com/ajthemacboy/a948fa59dc30a0569440bc13d6983f85",
